  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: knowledge-grader (npm)",
  "details": "The package runs a preinstall hook that executes index.js. The script collects system information (hostname, home directory, username, DNS server addresses, /etc/passwd contents, and /etc/hosts contents) from the installation machine and sends it via HTTPS POST to tebdjgz4guem6t74pf6iyowyjppgd71w[.]oastify[.]com (a Burp Collaborator / oastify C2 endpoint). The exfiltrated data includes the full /etc/passwd file, which contains user account metadata.",
